-- Colombian Stock Movers: Empresa de Telecomunicaciones, Ecopetrol
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-02-08T21:16:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/colombian-stock-movers-empresa-de-telecomunicaciones-ecopetrol.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 0.2 percent to 14,052.98, while the
Colcap Index rose 0.3 percent to 1,655.43.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
rose 0.1 percent to 4,685 pesos.  Colombia is in “no rush” to sell its stake in Ecopetrol,
Finance Minister Juan Carlos Echeverry said today on a
conference call with investors.  The country has a lot of other assets it can sell,
including electricity companies, and is neither “rushing” nor
“stopping” its program of privatizations, Echeverry said.  The company will also finish maintenance work on the
Cartagena refinery on the Caribbean coast at the end of this
month, a company official who can’t be cited because of
corporate policy, said today by telephone.  Empresa de Telecomunicaciones de Bogota SA  (ETB CB), the
city-run phone company serving  Colombia ’s capital, fell 1.4
percent to 481 pesos, a two-week low.  Colombia’s comptroller’s office is reviewing alleged
irregular retirement payments to former employees of ETB, as the
company is known, RCN radio reported yesterday. ETB said it
hasn’t been notified by the comptroller’s office regarding the
review of the payments, according to a regulatory filing today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
